'''''Young and Rich''''' is the second [[album]] by [[The Tubes]], released in 1976.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2009/02/the-tubes-young-and-rich.html|title=The Tubes - Young and Rich|date=September 14, 2015|website=www.pastemagazine.com}}</ref> It reached #46 on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' 200.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-vDgDAAAQBAJ&pg=PT49&lpg=PT49&dq=Young+and+Rich+the+tubes+1976+a&m&source=bl&ots=KUcJdA4T43&sig=ACfU3U0ZaoRCeR6O-zDYUfk06Xb2TOsOkQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwizu7ya7LXmAhVCcq0KHRsgDDk4FBDoATAGegQIChAB#v=onepage&q=Young+and+Rich+the+tubes+1976+a&m&f=false|title=Terminated for Reasons of Taste: Other Ways to Hear Essential and Inessential Music|first=Chuck|last=Eddy|date=August 25, 2016|publisher=Duke University Press|via=Google Books}}</ref>
The album is no longer available on CD, although all of its songs can be found on ''White Punks on Dope''.
==Track listing== #"Tubes World Tour" (Spooner, Steen, Waybill) – 4:43 #"Brighter Day" (Steen) – 3:39 #"Pimp" (Spooner) – 4:27 #"Stand Up and Shout" (Ray Trainer, Mike Condello) – 2:37 #"Don't Touch Me There" (Ron Nagle, [[Jane Dornacker]]) – 3:30 #"Slipped My Disco" (Spooner, Steen) – 4:27 #"Proud to Be an American" (Spooner) – 2:58 #"Poland Whole/Madam I'm Adam" (Steen, Spooner, The Tubes) – 6:30 #"Young and Rich" (Spooner) – 5:07
==Personnel== *[[Fee Waybill]] - vocals *[[Bill Spooner|Bill "Sputnik" Spooner]] - guitar, vocals *Roger Steen - guitar, harp, vocals *Rick "Gator" Anderson - bass, vocals *[[Vince Welnick]] - keyboards, synthesizer *Michael Cotten - synthesizer *[[Prairie Prince|"Preposterous" Prairie Prince]] - percussion *Re Styles (Shirley MacLeod) - "funky-pretty" vocals with: *[[David Paich]], [[Jack Nitzsche]] - arrangements *[[Chuck Domanico]] - bass *[[Don Randi]] - piano *Alan Estes, [[Julius Wechter]] - percussion *[[Jay Migliori]], [[Steve Douglas (saxophonist)|Steve Douglas]] - saxophone *[[Bobby Shew]] - trumpet *[[George Bohanon]] - trombone *[[Deniece Williams]], Julia Tillman Waters, Maxine Williard Waters, The Ron Hicklin Singers - backing vocals *Allan Harshman, Assa Drori, Harry Bluestone, Herschel Wise, James Getzoff, Jesse Ehrlich, Leonard Malarsky, Lou Klass, Marshall Sosson, Marvin Limonick, Murray Adler, Nathan Ross, Ray Kelley, Samuel Boghossian, Virginia Majewski, William Kurasch - strings *Armand Kaproff, David Speltz - cello ;Technical *Ed Thacker - engineer *Michael Cotten, Prairie Prince - album design *Harry Mittman, [[Norman Seeff]] - photography
==Covers== *[[Lizzy Borden (band)|Lizzy Borden]] covered "Don't Touch Me There" on their ''Terror Rising'' EP.
